# TRANSLATOR ChatGPT
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:28
#, no-wrap
msgid "It turned out that merely changing the sign of the diffusion partial derivative equation update could actually sharpen the image. I had worked on blind deconvolution for years when I started working on a diffusion model, and never managed to make even the _state-of-the-art_ method work outside of the nice poster cases (low ISO, low saturation, uniform blur). But this of course needed a regularization parameter to avoid diverging. \n"
msgstr "Il s'est avéré que le simple fait de changer le signe de la mise à jour de l'équation aux dérivées partielles de diffusion pouvait en réalité accentuer la netteté de l'image. J'avais travaillé pendant des années sur la déconvolution aveugle lorsque j'ai commencé à travailler sur un modèle de diffusion, sans jamais réussir à faire fonctionner correctement, hors des beaux cas d'école, même la méthode _state-of-the-art_ : faible ISO, faible saturation, flou uniforme. Mais cela nécessitait bien sûr un paramètre de régularisation pour éviter la divergence. \n"

# TRANSLATOR ChatGPT
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "This is how the _diffuse or sharpen_ module was born, as a generic framework for all sorts of diffusive or counter-diffusive phenomenon simulation.\n"
msgstr "C'est ainsi qu'est né le module _diffuse or sharpen_, comme cadre générique de simulation de toutes sortes de phénomènes diffusifs ou contre-diffusifs.\n"

# TRANSLATOR ChatGPT
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:34
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{{< note >}}\n"
"In the following, we will use the vocabulary of Fourier harmonic analysis (especially _frequency_) even though we are not strictly in a such framework, but the wavelets scheme is very close in principle from a signal decomposition into Fourier harmonic series.\n"
"{{< /note >}}\n"
msgstr ""
"{{< note >}}\n"
"Dans la suite, nous utiliserons le vocabulaire de l'analyse harmonique de Fourier, en particulier _fréquence_, même si nous ne sommes pas strictement dans ce cadre, car le schéma en ondelettes est très proche en principe d'une décomposition du signal en série harmonique de Fourier.\n"
"{{< /note >}}\n"

# TRANSLATOR ChatGPT
#. type: Title ##
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:35
#, no-wrap
msgid "Continuous model"
msgstr "Modèle continu"

# TRANSLATOR ChatGPT
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:38
#, no-wrap
msgid "At heart, the module implements a family of anisotropic diffusion equations of the form\n"
msgstr "Au coeur du module, on trouve une famille d'équations de diffusion anisotrope de la forme\n"

# TRANSLATOR ChatGPT
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:42
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$$\n"
"\\partial_t u = \\nabla \\cdot (\\mathbf{A} \\nabla u),\n"
"$$\n"
msgstr ""
"$$\n"
"\\partial_t u = \\nabla \\cdot (\\mathbf{A} \\nabla u),\n"
"$$\n"

# TRANSLATOR ChatGPT
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:44
#, no-wrap
msgid "where $u$ is the image and $\\mathbf{A}$ is a symmetric positive diffusion tensor that steers the smoothing either along the isophotes, along the gradient, or isotropically.[^qin][^witkin91]\n"
msgstr "où $u$ est l'image et $\\mathbf{A}$ un tenseur de diffusion symétrique positif qui oriente le lissage soit le long des isophotes, soit le long du gradient, soit de manière isotrope.[^qin][^witkin91]\n"

# TRANSLATOR ChatGPT
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:46
#, no-wrap
msgid "The original inspiration in the code is the inpainting model of Qin et al., who couple image structure and texture restoration through anisotropic heat transfer.[^qin] Ansel keeps that spirit, but applies the PDE in a wavelet domain, separately on low-frequency and high-frequency bands, and exposes four user-controlled transport coefficients.\n"
msgstr "L'inspiration d'origine dans le code est le modèle de retouche de Qin et al., qui couple structure de l'image et restauration de texture au moyen d'un transfert thermique anisotrope.[^qin] Ansel en conserve l'esprit, mais applique l'EDP dans un domaine en ondelettes, séparément sur les bandes de basse et de haute fréquence, et expose quatre coefficients de transport contrôlés par l'utilisateur.\n"

# TRANSLATOR ChatGPT
#. type: Title ##
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:47
#, no-wrap
msgid "Discrete gradients and anisotropy"
msgstr "Gradients discrets et anisotropie"

# TRANSLATOR ChatGPT
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:50
#, no-wrap
msgid "For each pixel and each channel, the module extracts a 3x3 neighborhood and evaluates centered first derivatives\n"
msgstr "Pour chaque pixel et chaque canal, le module extrait un voisinage 3x3 et évalue les dérivées premières centrées\n"

# TRANSLATOR ChatGPT
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:57
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$$\n"
"\\begin{align}\n"
"g_x &= \\frac{u(i+1,j) - u(i-1,j)}{2} \\\\\\\n"
"g_y &= \\frac{u(i,j+1) - u(i,j-1)}{2}\n"
"\\end{align}\n"
"$$\n"
msgstr ""
"$$\n"
"\\begin{align}\n"
"g_x &= \\frac{u(i+1,j) - u(i-1,j)}{2} \\\\\\\n"
"g_y &= \\frac{u(i,j+1) - u(i,j-1)}{2}\n"
"\\end{align}\n"
"$$\n"

# TRANSLATOR ChatGPT
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:59
#, no-wrap
msgid "This is the standard central-difference gradient used in discrete scale-space and diffusion methods.[^witkin83]\n"
msgstr "Il s'agit du gradient standard à différences centrées utilisé dans les méthodes discrètes d'espace d'échelle et de diffusion.[^witkin83]\n"

# TRANSLATOR ChatGPT
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:61
#, no-wrap
msgid "The local gradient orientation is then :\n"
msgstr "L'orientation locale du gradient est alors :\n"

# TRANSLATOR ChatGPT
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:70
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$$\n"
"\\begin{align}\n"
"\\cos\\theta =\n"
"\\frac{g_x}{\\sqrt{g_x^2 + g_y^2}} \\\\\\\n"
"\\sin\\theta =\n"
"\\frac{g_y}{\\sqrt{g_x^2 + g_y^2}}\n"
"\\end{align}\n"
"$$\n"
msgstr ""
"$$\n"
"\\begin{align}\n"
"\\cos\\theta =\n"
"\\frac{g_x}{\\sqrt{g_x^2 + g_y^2}} \\\\\\\n"
"\\sin\\theta =\n"
"\\frac{g_y}{\\sqrt{g_x^2 + g_y^2}}\n"
"\\end{align}\n"
"$$\n"

# TRANSLATOR ChatGPT
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:72
#, no-wrap
msgid "with the usual fallback to $(1,0)$ when the gradient magnitude vanishes.[^impl] Note that we will avoid computing the expensive $\\theta$ angle as the $\\arctan2$ function of the $(x, y)$ components, since it will never be used directly in the following.\n"
msgstr "avec le repli habituel vers $(1,0)$ lorsque la norme du gradient s'annule.[^impl] Notons que nous éviterons de calculer l'angle coûteux $\\theta$ comme fonction $\\arctan2$ des composantes $(x, y)$, puisqu'il ne sera jamais utilisé directement dans la suite.\n"

# TRANSLATOR ChatGPT
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:74
#, no-wrap
msgid "The anisotropy strength is converted from the user parameter $a$ into a positive coefficient\n"
msgstr "L'intensité de l'anisotropie est convertie à partir du paramètre utilisateur $a$ en un coefficient positif\n"

# TRANSLATOR ChatGPT
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:78
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$$\n"
"\\alpha = a^2,\n"
"$$\n"
msgstr ""
"$$\n"
"\\alpha = a^2,\n"
"$$\n"

# TRANSLATOR ChatGPT
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:80
#, no-wrap
msgid "while the sign of $a$ selects the mode:\n"
msgstr "tandis que le signe de $a$ sélectionne le mode :\n"

# TRANSLATOR ChatGPT
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:84
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"* $a = 0$: isotropic diffusion,\n"
"* $a > 0$: diffusion aligned with the isophote direction,\n"
"* $a < 0$: diffusion aligned with the gradient direction.[^impl]\n"
msgstr ""
"* $a = 0$ : diffusion isotrope,\n"
"* $a > 0$ : diffusion alignée avec la direction des isophotes,\n"
"* $a < 0$ : diffusion alignée avec la direction du gradient.[^impl]\n"

# TRANSLATOR ChatGPT
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:86
#, no-wrap
msgid "The damping term is then\n"
msgstr "Le terme d'amortissement est alors\n"

# TRANSLATOR ChatGPT
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:90
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$$\n"
"c^2 = \\exp(-\\alpha \\lVert \\nabla u \\rVert),\n"
"$$\n"
msgstr ""
"$$\n"
"c^2 = \\exp(-\\alpha \\lVert \\nabla u \\rVert),\n"
"$$\n"

# TRANSLATOR ChatGPT
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:92
#, no-wrap
msgid "which matches the anisotropic diffusion of Qin et al. for inpainting.[^qin]\n"
msgstr "ce qui correspond à la diffusion anisotrope de Qin et al. pour la retouche.[^qin]\n"

# TRANSLATOR ChatGPT
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:94
#, no-wrap
msgid "For isophote-aligned diffusion, the tensor written in the local image basis is :\n"
msgstr "Pour une diffusion alignée sur les isophotes, le tenseur écrit dans la base locale de l'image est :\n"

# TRANSLATOR ChatGPT
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:102
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$$\n"
"\\mathbf{A}_{\\perp} =\n"
"\\begin{bmatrix}\n"
"\\cos^2\\theta + c^2 \\sin^2\\theta & (c^2 - 1)\\cos\\theta\\sin\\theta \\\\\\\n"
"(c^2 - 1)\\cos\\theta\\sin\\theta & c^2 \\cos^2\\theta + \\sin^2\\theta\n"
"\\end{bmatrix}.\n"
"$$\n"
msgstr ""
"$$\n"
"\\mathbf{A}_{\\perp} =\n"
"\\begin{bmatrix}\n"
"\\cos^2\\theta + c^2 \\sin^2\\theta & (c^2 - 1)\\cos\\theta\\sin\\theta \\\\\\\n"
"(c^2 - 1)\\cos\\theta\\sin\\theta & c^2 \\cos^2\\theta + \\sin^2\\theta\n"
"\\end{bmatrix}.\n"
"$$\n"

# TRANSLATOR ChatGPT
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:104
#, no-wrap
msgid "For gradient-aligned diffusion, Ansel uses the inverted form :\n"
msgstr "Pour une diffusion alignée sur le gradient, Ansel utilise la forme inversée :\n"

# TRANSLATOR ChatGPT
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:112
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$$\n"
"\\mathbf{A}_{\\parallel} =\n"
"\\begin{bmatrix}\n"
"c^2 \\cos^2\\theta + \\sin^2\\theta & (1 - c^2)\\cos\\theta\\sin\\theta \\\\\\\n"
"(1 - c^2)\\cos\\theta\\sin\\theta & \\cos^2\\theta + c^2 \\sin^2\\theta\n"
"\\end{bmatrix}.\n"
"$$\n"
msgstr ""
"$$\n"
"\\mathbf{A}_{\\parallel} =\n"
"\\begin{bmatrix}\n"
"c^2 \\cos^2\\theta + \\sin^2\\theta & (1 - c^2)\\cos\\theta\\sin\\theta \\\\\\\n"
"(1 - c^2)\\cos\\theta\\sin\\theta & \\cos^2\\theta + c^2 \\sin^2\\theta\n"
"\\end{bmatrix}.\n"
"$$\n"

# TRANSLATOR ChatGPT
#. type: Title ##
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:113
#, no-wrap
msgid "The 3x3 diffusion stencils"
msgstr "Les stencils de diffusion 3x3"

# TRANSLATOR Claude
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:116
#, no-wrap
msgid "Depending on user parameters, we will evaluate for each pixel the $\\mathbf{K(A)}$ stencil using one of the $\\mathbf{A}$ tensors above.\n"
msgstr "Selon les paramètres de l'utilisateur, nous évaluerons pour chaque pixel le stencil $\\mathbf{K(A)}$ en utilisant l'un des tenseurs $\\mathbf{A}$ ci-dessus.\n"

# TRANSLATOR Claude
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:118
#, no-wrap
msgid "Given the symmetric tensor $\\mathbf{A}$ :\n"
msgstr "Étant donné le tenseur symétrique $\\mathbf{A}$ :\n"

# TRANSLATOR Claude
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:126
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$$\n"
"\\mathbf{A} =\n"
"\\begin{bmatrix}\n"
"a_{11} & a_{12} \\\\\\\n"
"a_{12} & a_{22}\n"
"\\end{bmatrix},\n"
"$$\n"
msgstr ""
"$$\n"
"\\mathbf{A} =\n"
"\\begin{bmatrix}\n"
"a_{11} & a_{12} \\\\\\\n"
"a_{12} & a_{22}\n"
"\\end{bmatrix},\n"
"$$\n"

# TRANSLATOR Claude
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:128
#, no-wrap
msgid "we build the discrete, rotated, anisotropic Laplacian kernel $\\nabla \\cdot (\\mathbf{A}\\nabla u)$ as the 3x3 stencil :\n"
msgstr "nous construisons le noyau laplacien discret, tourné et anisotrope $\\nabla \\cdot (\\mathbf{A}\\nabla u)$ sous forme du stencil 3x3 :\n"

# TRANSLATOR Claude
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:137
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$$\n"
"\\mathbf{K}(\\mathbf{A}) =\n"
"\\begin{bmatrix}\n"
"\\frac{a_{12}}{2} & a_{22} & -\\frac{a_{12}}{2} \\\\\\\n"
"a_{11} & -2(a_{11}+a_{22}) & a_{11} \\\\\\\n"
"-\\frac{a_{12}}{2} & a_{22} & \\frac{a_{12}}{2}\n"
"\\end{bmatrix},\n"
"$$\n"
msgstr ""
"$$\n"
"\\mathbf{K}(\\mathbf{A}) =\n"
"\\begin{bmatrix}\n"
"\\frac{a_{12}}{2} & a_{22} & -\\frac{a_{12}}{2} \\\\\\\n"
"a_{11} & -2(a_{11}+a_{22}) & a_{11} \\\\\\\n"
"-\\frac{a_{12}}{2} & a_{22} & \\frac{a_{12}}{2}\n"
"\\end{bmatrix},\n"
"$$\n"

# TRANSLATOR Claude
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:139
#, no-wrap
msgid "up to the sign convention mentioned in the source code for the off-diagonal terms.[^qin][^witkin91][^impl]\n"
msgstr "à la convention de signe près mentionnée dans le code source pour les termes hors diagonale.[^qin][^witkin91][^impl]\n"

# TRANSLATOR Claude
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:141
#, no-wrap
msgid "In the isotropic case expands to a constant :\n"
msgstr "Dans le cas isotrope, il se réduit à une constante :\n"

# TRANSLATOR Claude
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:150
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$$\n"
"\\mathbf{K}_{\\text{iso}} =\n"
"\\begin{bmatrix}\n"
"\\tfrac14 & \\tfrac12 & \\tfrac14 \\\\\\\n"
"\\tfrac12 & -3 & \\tfrac12 \\\\\\\n"
"\\tfrac14 & \\tfrac12 & \\tfrac14\n"
"\\end{bmatrix},\n"
"$$\n"
msgstr ""
"$$\n"
"\\mathbf{K}_{\\text{iso}} =\n"
"\\begin{bmatrix}\n"
"\\tfrac14 & \\tfrac12 & \\tfrac14 \\\\\\\n"
"\\tfrac12 & -3 & \\tfrac12 \\\\\\\n"
"\\tfrac14 & \\tfrac12 & \\tfrac14\n"
"\\end{bmatrix},\n"
"$$\n"

# TRANSLATOR Claude
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:152
#, no-wrap
msgid "which is the classical Oono-Puri style isotropic Laplacian. Its interest is rotational behavior: compared with the 5-point Laplacian, the angular error is reduced, which matters when diffusion must not privilege the image axes.[^oono][^patra] This angular error was evaluated against similar kernels in [_Rotation-invariant Laplacian for 2D grids_](https://eng.aurelienpierre.com/2021/03/rotation-invariant-laplacian-for-2d-grids/).\n"
msgstr "qui est le laplacien isotrope classique de type Oono-Puri. Son intérêt réside dans son comportement rotationnel : comparé au laplacien à 5 points, l'erreur angulaire est réduite, ce qui importe lorsque la diffusion ne doit pas privilégier les axes de l'image.[^oono][^patra] Cette erreur angulaire a été évaluée face à des noyaux similaires dans [_Rotation-invariant Laplacian for 2D grids_](https://eng.aurelienpierre.com/2021/03/rotation-invariant-laplacian-for-2d-grids/).\n"

# TRANSLATOR Claude
#. type: Plain text
#: content/resources/diffuse-or-sharpen-math/index.md:154
#, no-wrap
