msgid ""
"Color Correction Handbook (vol. 1) / Color Correction Look Book (vol 2). Alexis Van Hurkman. 2013. [Google Play vol. 1](https://books.google.fr/books?id=kDcdAgAAQBAJ). [Google Play vol. 2](https://books.google.fr/books?id=Hm9VAgAAQBAJ)\n"
": These books have a special place in Darktable/Ansel history because I used them as a reference to redesign the features of the [color balance](/doc/views/darkroom/modules/color-balance-rgb/) module. While they focus on color grading for movies, they are software-agnostic (showing how to get things done in different applications), and make use of color tools like RGB curves, color balance, channel mixer and 3D LUTs that are all available in Ansel. They contain valuable insight on how to (and why) create color looks in images, to put the form at the service of the content. I recommend you get digital copies of them because they have lots of illustrations that will be rendered on screen better than what printed paper allows.\n"
msgstr ""
